<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2"><Document><name>UFO Timeline Project - Google Earth</name><Style id="ufoPinStyle"><IconStyle><scale>1.1</scale><Icon><href>https://utp-creator.github.io/utp-maps/UFO-PIN.png</href></Icon></IconStyle><LabelStyle><scale>0.8</scale></LabelStyle></Style><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Roswell 1947 UFO Case (Debris/Crash)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Roswell 1947 UFO Case (Debris/Crash)</strong><br/>Roswell, NM, US<br/>Tue Jul 08 1947 04:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Debris/Crash<br/><br/>A rancher found unusual debris on his property near Roswell, New Mexico in July 1947. Initially reported as a &#39;flying disc&#39; by the local military base before being retracted as a weather balloon, the event became the world&#39;s most famous UFO crash story.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-104.523,33.3943,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Mount Rainier area 1947 UFO Case (Disc/Saucer)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Mount Rainier area 1947 UFO Case (Disc/Saucer)</strong><br/>Mount Rainier area, WA, US<br/>Tue Jun 24 1947 04:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Disc/Saucer<br/><br/>Pilot Kenneth Arnold reported nine shiny, saucer-like objects flying in formation near Mount Rainier in 1947. His description of their movement led to the popularization of the term &#39;flying saucer&#39; in global media.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-121.7603,46.8523,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Washington 1952 UFO Case (Light/Radar-Visual)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Washington 1952 UFO Case (Light/Radar-Visual)</strong><br/>Washington, DC, US<br/>Sat Jul 19 1952 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Light/Radar-Visual<br/><br/>In July 1952, radar targets and visual reports over Washington, D.C. created one of the most publicized UFO waves of the early Cold War period. The events drew press attention, official response, and long-term debate over what was tracked above the capital.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-77.0369,38.9072,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>McMinnville 1950 UFO Case (Disc)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>McMinnville 1950 UFO Case (Disc)</strong><br/>McMinnville, OR, US<br/>Thu May 11 1950 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Disc<br/><br/>Paul and Evelyn Trent photographed a metallic disc-shaped object over their farm near McMinnville, Oregon in 1950. The two photographs became among the most analyzed and debated UFO images in history.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-123.1987,45.2108,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Lubbock 1951 UFO Case (Formation/Lights)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Lubbock 1951 UFO Case (Formation/Lights)</strong><br/>Lubbock, TX, US<br/>Sat Aug 25 1951 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Formation/Lights<br/><br/>Multiple witnesses including university professors observed V-shaped formations of bluish-green lights passing overhead near Lubbock, Texas in August 1951. The case became a benchmark for multi-witness formation sightings.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-101.8552,33.5779,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Lincoln area 1961 UFO Case (Star/Disc)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Lincoln area 1961 UFO Case (Star/Disc)</strong><br/>Lincoln area, NH, US<br/>Tue Sep 19 1961 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Star/Disc<br/><br/>Betty and Barney Hill reported being followed and abducted by a craft while driving through New Hampshire in September 1961. Their account became the first widely publicized abduction narrative in modern UFO history.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-71.6701,44.0409,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Socorro 1964 UFO Case (Egg/Oval)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Socorro 1964 UFO Case (Egg/Oval)</strong><br/>Socorro, NM, US<br/>Fri Apr 24 1964 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Egg/Oval<br/><br/>Police officer Lonnie Zamora reported observing an egg-shaped craft and two small humanoid figures near Socorro, New Mexico in 1964. Physical landing traces were documented, making it a key case for Project Blue Book.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-106.8914,34.0584,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Exeter 1965 UFO Case (Sphere/Light)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Exeter 1965 UFO Case (Sphere/Light)</strong><br/>Exeter, NH, US<br/>Fri Sep 03 1965 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Sphere/Light<br/><br/>Multiple witnesses including police officers reported a large, low-flying object with bright pulsating lights near Exeter, New Hampshire in 1965. The event became one of the most credible police-witnessed UFO cases.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-70.9478,42.9815,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Shag Harbour 1967 UFO Case (Unknown/Water-impact)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Shag Harbour 1967 UFO Case (Unknown/Water-impact)</strong><br/>Shag Harbour, Nova Scotia, Canada<br/>Wed Oct 04 1967 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Unknown/Water-impact<br/><br/>Witnesses observed a luminous object descend and apparently impact the waters off Shag Harbour, Nova Scotia in October 1967. A subsequent search by Royal Canadian Mounted Police and Navy made it Canada&#39;s most documented water-impact UFO case.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-65.7236,43.7219,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Pascagoula 1973 UFO Case (Unknown/Oval)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Pascagoula 1973 UFO Case (Unknown/Oval)</strong><br/>Pascagoula, MS, US<br/>Thu Oct 11 1973 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Unknown/Oval<br/><br/>Charles Hickson and Calvin Parker reported being abducted by humanoid beings while fishing along the Pascagoula River in Mississippi in October 1973. Their account is a defining case of the 1973 wave.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-88.5561,30.3658,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Nuremberg 1561 UFO Case (Multi/Sphere)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Nuremberg 1561 UFO Case (Multi/Sphere)</strong><br/>Nuremberg, Bavaria, Germany<br/>Fri Apr 14 1561 02:56:56 GMT-0456 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Multi/Sphere<br/><br/>A broadside printed in Nuremberg in April 1561 described a mass aerial phenomenon involving spheres, cylinders, and crosses appearing to battle in the sky over the city at sunrise.]]></description><Point><coordinates>11.0767,49.4521,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Basel 1566 UFO Case (Sphere/Dark)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Basel 1566 UFO Case (Sphere/Dark)</strong><br/>Basel, Switzerland<br/>Sun Aug 07 1566 02:56:56 GMT-0456 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Sphere/Dark<br/><br/>A 1566 Basel broadsheet illustration depicted large black spheres seen in the sky over the city, described as appearing to move and collide at sunrise on multiple consecutive days.]]></description><Point><coordinates>7.5886,47.5596,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Denison 1878 UFO Case (Daylight Object)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Denison 1878 UFO Case (Daylight Object)</strong><br/>Denison, TX, US<br/>Fri Jan 25 1878 02:56:56 GMT-0456 (Eastern Standard Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Daylight Object<br/><br/>Farmer John Martin reported observing a fast-moving dark object resembling a balloon traveling at high speed near Denison, Texas in 1878, in what is often cited as one of the earliest documented uses of the word &#39;saucer&#39; to describe an aerial object.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-96.5367,33.7557,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Multiple 1896 UFO Case (Airship/Light)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Multiple 1896 UFO Case (Airship/Light)</strong><br/>Multiple, CA, US<br/>Sun Nov 01 1896 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Airship/Light<br/><br/>Beginning in November 1896, witnesses across California and the western United States reported a mysterious lighted airship traveling overhead, sparking a multi-state press wave decades before the 1947 era.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-119.4179,36.7783,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Aurora 1897 UFO Case (Cigar/Crash)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Aurora 1897 UFO Case (Cigar/Crash)</strong><br/>Aurora, TX, US<br/>Sat Apr 17 1897 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Cigar/Crash<br/><br/>Local newspaper accounts described an airship crashing into a windmill in Aurora, Texas in April 1897, with reports of unusual wreckage and the burial of a non-human pilot at a local cemetery.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-97.5034,33.0584,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Los Angeles 1942 UFO Case (Object/Light)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Los Angeles 1942 UFO Case (Object/Light)</strong><br/>Los Angeles, CA, US<br/>Wed Feb 25 1942 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Standard Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Object/Light<br/><br/>In the early morning of February 25, 1942, U.S. anti-aircraft batteries fired more than 1,400 shells at unidentified objects in the skies over Los Angeles, an event captured in iconic searchlight photographs.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-118.2437,34.0522,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>European Theater 1944 UFO Case (Light/Orbs)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>European Theater 1944 UFO Case (Light/Orbs)</strong><br/>European Theater, Multiple<br/>Wed Nov 01 1944 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Light/Orbs<br/><br/>Allied and Axis pilots during World War II reported small, glowing balls of light pacing their aircraft over Europe and the Pacific, dubbed &#39;foo fighters&#39; by the press.]]></description><Point><coordinates>8.6821,50.1109,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Multiple 1946 UFO Case (Rocket/Cigar)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Multiple 1946 UFO Case (Rocket/Cigar)</strong><br/>Multiple, Sweden<br/>Wed May 01 1946 04:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Rocket/Cigar<br/><br/>From May 1946, observers across Sweden and other Scandinavian countries reported rocket- or cigar-shaped objects streaking through the sky, prompting a Swedish military investigation.]]></description><Point><coordinates>18.6435,60.1282,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Maury Island 1947 UFO Case (Donut/Debris)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Maury Island 1947 UFO Case (Donut/Debris)</strong><br/>Maury Island, WA, US<br/>Sat Jun 21 1947 04:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Donut/Debris<br/><br/>Harold Dahl reported a group of donut-shaped craft over Maury Island, Washington in June 1947, with claims of falling slag-like debris and an alleged Men in Black encounter that became foundational to UFO folklore.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-122.4435,47.377,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Multiple 1947 UFO Case (Disc)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Multiple 1947 UFO Case (Disc)</strong><br/>Multiple, US<br/>Tue Jun 24 1947 04:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Disc<br/><br/>Following Kenneth Arnold&#39;s June 1947 sighting, hundreds of &#39;flying disc&#39; reports surfaced across the United States in the summer of 1947, marking the launch of the modern UFO era.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-98.5795,39.8283,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Montgomery 1948 UFO Case (Torpedo/Cigar)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Montgomery 1948 UFO Case (Torpedo/Cigar)</strong><br/>Montgomery, AL, US<br/>Sat Jul 24 1948 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Torpedo/Cigar<br/><br/>Eastern Air Lines pilots Clarence Chiles and John Whitted reported a torpedo-shaped craft with windows passing their DC-3 near Montgomery, Alabama in July 1948.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-86.2999,32.3668,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Fargo 1948 UFO Case (Light/Sphere)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Fargo 1948 UFO Case (Light/Sphere)</strong><br/>Fargo, ND, US<br/>Fri Oct 01 1948 02:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Light/Sphere<br/><br/>National Guard pilot George Gorman reported an extended aerial pursuit of a maneuvering bright light over Fargo, North Dakota in October 1948, in what became known as the &#39;Gorman Dogfight&#39;.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-96.7898,46.8772,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Franklin 1948 UFO Case (Cone/Disc)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Franklin 1948 UFO Case (Cone/Disc)</strong><br/>Franklin, KY, US<br/>Wed Jan 07 1948 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Cone/Disc<br/><br/>Kentucky Air National Guard pilot Thomas Mantell died while pursuing an unidentified high-altitude object in January 1948, becoming the first widely reported pilot fatality associated with a UFO chase.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-86.5772,36.7223,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Great Falls 1950 UFO Case (Disc/Light)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Great Falls 1950 UFO Case (Disc/Light)</strong><br/>Great Falls, MT, US<br/>Tue Aug 15 1950 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Disc/Light<br/><br/>Nick Mariana, manager of the Great Falls baseball team, filmed two bright objects moving across the sky over Great Falls, Montana in August 1950, producing one of the earliest UFO motion picture films.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-111.3008,47.5053,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Flatwoods 1952 UFO Case (Sphere/Being)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Flatwoods 1952 UFO Case (Sphere/Being)</strong><br/>Flatwoods, WV, US<br/>Fri Sep 12 1952 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Sphere/Being<br/><br/>Witnesses near Flatwoods, West Virginia in September 1952 reported a glowing object descending into a hillside followed by an encounter with a tall, robed entity, an event that became a landmark cryptid-UFO case.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-80.6515,38.7212,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Hopkinsville 1955 UFO Case (Light/Beings)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Hopkinsville 1955 UFO Case (Light/Beings)</strong><br/>Hopkinsville, KY, US<br/>Sun Aug 21 1955 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Light/Beings<br/><br/>The Sutton family near Kelly, Kentucky reported a prolonged August 1955 siege by small, glowing humanoid beings around their farmhouse, one of the most famous close encounters of the third kind.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-87.4886,36.8656,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Levelland 1957 UFO Case (Egg/Oval)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Levelland 1957 UFO Case (Egg/Oval)</strong><br/>Levelland, TX, US<br/>Sat Nov 02 1957 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Egg/Oval<br/><br/>Multiple drivers near Levelland, Texas in November 1957 reported large egg-shaped objects on or near roadways with simultaneous vehicle ignition failures, a defining electromagnetic-effect case.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-102.378,33.5873,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Kecksburg 1965 UFO Case (Acorn/Crash)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Kecksburg 1965 UFO Case (Acorn/Crash)</strong><br/>Kecksburg, PA, US<br/>Thu Dec 09 1965 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Acorn/Crash<br/><br/>Witnesses reported an acorn-shaped object descending into woods near Kecksburg, Pennsylvania in December 1965, followed by a heavy military presence and recovery operation.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-79.4611,40.1848,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Clayton South 1966 UFO Case (Saucer)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Clayton South 1966 UFO Case (Saucer)</strong><br/>Clayton South, Victoria, Australia<br/>Wed Apr 06 1966 03:00:00 GMT-0500 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Saucer<br/><br/>More than two hundred students and teachers at Westall High School near Clayton South, Victoria observed a saucer-shaped craft descend, land briefly, and depart in April 1966, Australia&#39;s most prominent mass-witness UFO case.]]></description><Point><coordinates>145.1167,-37.9333,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><styleUrl>#ufoPinStyle</styleUrl><name>Lake Cote area 1971 UFO Case (Disc/Aerial Mapping)</name><description><![CDATA[<strong>Lake Cote area 1971 UFO Case (Disc/Aerial Mapping)</strong><br/>Lake Cote area, Alajuela, Costa Rica<br/>Sat Sep 04 1971 03:00:00 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)<br/><strong>Shape:</strong> Disc/Aerial Mapping<br/><br/>A Costa Rican government aerial mapping survey on September 4, 1971 captured a metallic disc-shaped object over Lake Cote, producing one of the highest-resolution and best-provenance UFO photographs on record.]]></description><Point><coordinates>-84.9167,10.5833,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Document></kml>